                <h1>Understanding the Equality Symbol: Meaning and Uses</h1>
                <p>The equality symbol (=) is a fundamental concept in mathematics and programming that signifies that two expressions are equal in value. It plays a crucial role in equations, logical statements, and algorithms. Understanding how to use the equality symbol helps in solving problems and forming accurate results in various fields.</p>
